latestPosts.caption:
Personal best in Paris 😭🫶🏻

This was honestly the best run of my life! 

When they mentioned that Paris marathon has the most scenic route of them all, I had no clue what to expect out of it. 

I have never felt so good while running, the weather, the views, and the incredible cheer support, everything was like a dream come true.

The whole plan was to run for the vibes and try to get a sub 4h30 finish. I didn’t want to put a-lot of pressure on me as it was my first international race but OH BOII, Your girl was flying😬

I felt so strong after the half marathon mark that I decided to go push my limits. This is the first time I have done a negative split. Shaved off 9 mins off my marathon time in 8 weeks with a total time of 04:26:31.

Couldn’t stop raving about how good @runna is to you guys. If you want to take your running journey to the next level, this is it! Use my code ‘OVERLYDAA’ or click the link in my bio for two free weeks. (Ad)

Love you @runna for the opportunity and for the best runners weekend ever! This one’s gonna be hard to beat!

House revamp✨😮‍💨

A little backstory! Rhythm and I have been living together for the past 4 years.

Our first apartment was a 1-room kitchen where having a sofa wasn’t even an option. We literally had to remove the bed just to fit a small one 😅

In the second apartment, we finally had the space… but no money to buy one, so we rented a sofa.

And now finally buying our first sofa, was honestly a little overwhelming.
After tons of research, we managed to get one that’s not exactly budget-friendly 😬 but it’s so comfy and looks super aesthetic too.

So yeah… really, really happy with this purchase 🥰

Couldn’t be more proud of my body for keeping up with me. I kept telling myself that 2025 was going to be bigger, and this challenge has been the cherry on top.
